@everyone I'm commandeering this channel to post the information on the equipment you got today.  I'll post one line per weapon and a single post afterward with all of the other equipment.

**Compound Bow**
Damage:  STR+1 Lethal (Requires 3 STR Min)
Range: Short Range (STR+Size+Athletics)x4    Medium Range (Short Rangex2)   Long Range (Medium Rangex2)
1 Turn to Reload (can only fire every other round)
Aiming Device (Reduces penalties for aiming by 2)
Broadhead carbon arrows (+1 to damage, cannot stake a vampire)
Bodkin Armon Piercing (wooden, reduces target's armor by 1, home-made)

*Example of play using Becca.  

Becca tries to shoot a deer to bring it down as it runs away at a distance.  Her STR is 3, Size is 5, ATH is 1.  9x4 is 36.  36x4 is 144 yards max distance (Becca can hit a target a football field and a half away).  She rolls a dice pool of DEX+ATH+(STR+1)+1(broadhead arrows) = 10 dice.  This pool is reduced by 4 dice for shooting at long range.  She still rolls 6 dice to hit the deer, rolling 2 successes and bringing it down so she can feed.

Becca attempts to stake Ian with her bodkin arrows at 30 yards (short range).  She is using her standard dice pool of DEX+ATH+(STR+1) = 9.  This will be reduced by 4 for aiming at the heart, but her aiming device makes it only 2.  She knows she'll need a minimum of 5 successes to get an actual stake (those are the rules), so she stacks the deck.  She activated Vigor earlier in the scene, adding 3 dice to her STR - her STR adds to her damage.  She also now spends a Willpower to add 3 more dice to this single roll.  That's 9-2+3+3=13 dice.   She'll need 5 successes to stake a vampire.*

**Crossbow**
Damage:  3L (2 STR required)
Range: 40/80/160
2 turns to reload with the included cocking device.  3 if this is lost or broken.
Scope equipped (reduced the penalty for shooting at Medium Range to nothing)

**Tuned Remington 700**
Damage: 4L 9 Again
Range: 250/500/1000
4 +1 clip
Scope equipped (reduces the penalty for shooting at Medium Range to nothing and at Long Range to -2)

**.44 Magnum Revolver "Live Free"**
Damage:  3L 9 Again
Range: 35/70/140
6 shots

**.38 Snub Police Edition**
Damage: 2L
Range: 20/40/80
5 shots

**Notes**
Bow, Crossbow, and Rifle have slings.  .38 snubs can be concealed in a pocket.  .44 Magnum can be concealed under a large jacket.   There are 2 .38 snubs

@everyone ((I'm going to use this channel to address three items for wrapup from today's session.  It's not technically roleplay, but it's roleplay-adjacent so there.  FIrst, I'll go over the timeline to get our head's straight.  Second, I'll discuss the ball location and vampire travel concerns.  Third, we'll deal with feeding.  

For timeline, I'm going to use dates as the date the evening you wake up.  I feel as if this simplifies things.  Therefore:

Nov. 30:  The mages touch base, you head to the distillery, you meet the werewolves, Ian takes the pub, you go to Max's apartment, you acquire new equipment.

Dec. 1: The team plans to overthrow Ian.  Becca and Zahir wash the car.  The team observes the pub via the security cameras

Dec 2:  The team attacks, Becca finds she's an excellent shot, Regina et. al. deliver a message from her father, they inherit a castle.

Dec. 3:  TBA

Dec. 4:  A celebratory ball is planned at Osterly House Estate in London.

Osterly House is on the outskirts of London.  When the team looks into travel, they'll find they essentially have three options.  

1.  Drive.  It takes 9 hours and 45 minutes to drive from Inverness to Osterly House.  They're expected at 8pm on Dec. 4th.  This is the safest option, but also the longest.  This option would pack them all in a car for a long time.  Also, they'd have to be careful not to draw attention.  The time listed above is for using highways - back roads would take longer.

2. Train.  It takes 8 hours and 30 minutes via train to get to London.  They will send a car to pick you up at the train station. This option is faster, but does coop you up in a train for a long time.  You'll need to make sure you aren't hungry!!  Also, that you don't act dumb.

3. Plane.  It's 1 hour and 30 minutes on a plane to get to London.  This option also requires *vampires* to get through *airport security*. Not to mention being cooped up in a flying box. Usually doesn't go well.  ))

((I'll be happy to handle any OOC questions and discussion about travel and feeding and timeline in here.  Feel free to grab a RP room and let me know for any feeding RP you'd like to do.  Same if anyone wants to do any RP regarding travel plans, etc.  NOTE:  It will take the rest of the current night to clean up after taking down Ian, chase off any remaining bag guys, board up the door, and settle into the pub))
Also, here's the document from earlier:

((Due to Max being a workaholic and dealing with other issues, Becca will be making travel plans. No matter how much Becca enjoys driving, 10 hours of driving is exhausting in any circumstance, and she is NOT trusting anyone but herself with Peregrine's car. So, she would probably plan to take the train on December 3rd at around 10 PM (that gives them 10 hours to get to the castle where the ball will be held before it gets light). They will then spend the following day sleeping at the castle, and wake up in time the next night to explore and get ready for the ball.

Now, Becca offers two options regarding travel (and since this travel is at night, everyone will be naturally awake for it):

1) Anyone who is below 7 humanity HAS to use a vitae to look more humanlike and blend in with the people on the train (this applies to Moonshine and Max). The goal here is to look as natural as possible and blend in.

2. The stake method. Becca lines the vampires up on a wall and shoots anyone willing in the chest with a wooden arrow (this can either be because you think it's a funny method of travel that your character would pursue, you don't want to spend a vitae, you are hungry for some reason, or you just think your character would be too nervous to travel on a train). Then, she puts them in a wooden crate and loads them as train cargo. She takes them out of torpor when they get to the castle (or at another convenient time), and tada, you are in London.

Keep in mind that Mr. King intends to start our next session at the ball, so any roleplay anyone would want to do regarding the trip would have to be done before then via Discord. Still, please let me know here your character's decisions so that you either adjust your vitae accordingly, or everyone just knows how they all got there. Thanks!))

*Moonshine feels an electric shock course through his body, starting at his forehead mark.  He collapses inward, focusing on his Auspex abilities, condensing all willpower left within on a singular goal of reaching out...*
